cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with large scale vision tasks and proposes a novel method for training convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised data sets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with natural language processing tasks (hashtag prediction), which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a unified feature embedding space, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
